---
import Base from '../../../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import Callout from '../../../../components/Callout.astro';
import AdSlot from '../../../../components/AdSlot.astro';
import Mastery from '../../../../components/Mastery.astro';
import TrustRow from '../../../../components/TrustRow.astro';
import { attempt } from '../../../../data/site.js';
---

<Base title="Goodwill: nature & valuation — Advanced Accounting Ch 4" active="papers">
  <main class="page" style="max-width: 1024px;">
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 48px; justify-content: center; align-items: flex-start;">
      <article style="max-width: 640px; min-width: 0; flex: 1;">
        <Breadcrumb crumbs={[
          { label: 'CA Intermediate', href: '/intermediate/' },
          { label: 'Paper 1 · Adv. Accounting', href: '/intermediate/advanced-accounting/' },
          { label: 'Ch 4 · Partnership', href: '/intermediate/advanced-accounting/' },
          { label: 'Goodwill: nature & valuation' },
        ]} />

        <h1 style="margin: 0; font-size: 30px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.01em; line-height: 1.25;">Goodwill: nature &amp; valuation</h1>
        <div style="margin: 12px 0 8px;">
          <TrustRow attempt={attempt.name} updated="30 Jun 2026" source="ICAI SM Mod 2, Unit 2; AS 26" />
        </div>
        <div style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-3); margin-bottom: 24px;">About 10 min read · 2 worked examples</div>

        <div class="article">
          <p>
            Goodwill is the value of a firm's reputation — the extra earning power that lets it make more
            than a normal return on its capital. Two things matter for the exam: <strong>when goodwill can
            be recorded</strong> (almost never) and <strong>how it is valued</strong> (four standard methods).
          </p>

          <h2 id="s1">1. Nature: when goodwill enters the books</h2>
          <p>
            Under AS 26, <strong>self-generated goodwill is never recognised</strong> as an asset — there is
            no measurable cost. Goodwill is recorded only when it is <em>purchased</em>: consideration in
            money or money's worth has been paid for it. On reconstitution (admission, retirement, death),
            goodwill is therefore <em>adjusted through capital accounts</em>, not raised as an asset.
          </p>

          <Callout kind="mistake">
            <p>
              Passing the entry "Goodwill A/c Dr … To Old Partners" on admission. Raising self-generated
              goodwill violates AS 26 — the premium is adjusted through partners' capital accounts in the
              sacrificing ratio instead.
            </p>
          </Callout>

          <h2 id="s2">2. Average profit method</h2>
          <p>
            Goodwill = average maintainable profit × number of years' purchase. Adjust the profits first:
            remove abnormal gains/losses and non-operating items; add back partner salaries only if the
            question treats them as appropriations.
          </p>

          <Callout kind="example" label="Worked example 1">
            <p>Profits of the last four years: ₹80,000 · ₹1,00,000 · ₹90,000 · ₹1,10,000. Value goodwill at 3 years' purchase of average profits.</p>
            <div class="working-note">
              <div class="working-note-label">Working note 1 — average profit</div>
              Average profit = (80,000 + 1,00,000 + 90,000 + 1,10,000) ÷ 4 = <strong>₹95,000</strong><br />
              Goodwill = 95,000 × 3 = <strong>₹2,85,000</strong>
            </div>
          </Callout>

          <h2 id="s3">3. Super profit method</h2>
          <p>
            Super profit = average profit − normal profit, where normal profit = capital employed × normal
            rate of return. Goodwill = super profit × years' purchase.
          </p>

          <Callout kind="example" label="Worked example 2">
            <p>Capital employed ₹5,00,000; normal rate of return 10%; average profit ₹95,000 (above). Value goodwill at 3 years' purchase of super profits.</p>
            <div class="working-note">
              <div class="working-note-label">Working note 1 — super profit</div>
              Normal profit = 5,00,000 × 10% = <strong>₹50,000</strong><br />
              Super profit = 95,000 − 50,000 = <strong>₹45,000</strong><br />
              Goodwill = 45,000 × 3 = <strong>₹1,35,000</strong>
            </div>
          </Callout>
        </div>

        <AdSlot />

        <div class="article">
          <h2 id="s4" style="margin-top: 0;">4. Capitalisation methods</h2>
          <p>
            <strong>Capitalisation of average profits:</strong> firm's implied value = average profit ÷ normal
            rate; goodwill = implied value − actual capital employed.<br />
            <strong>Capitalisation of super profits:</strong> goodwill = super profit ÷ normal rate.
            With the figures above: 45,000 ÷ 10% = ₹4,50,000.
          </p>

          <Callout kind="pointer">
            <p>
              Read which method the question demands — "years' purchase of super profits" and
              "capitalisation of super profits" use the same inputs and produce different answers.
              A one-line statement of the method earns the first mark.
            </p>
          </Callout>

          <Callout kind="mistake">
            <p>
              Using closing capital as capital employed. Unless the question says otherwise, use
              <strong>average</strong> capital employed, and exclude non-trade investments from it —
              their income isn't part of operating profit either.
            </p>
          </Callout>
        </div>

        <div style="border-top: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 32px; padding-top: 20px;">
          <a href="/practice/quiz/?topic=partnership" class="btn btn-primary">Practice partnership topics</a>
          <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; margin-top: 24px; gap: 16px;">
            <span style="flex: 1;"></span>
            <a href="/intermediate/advanced-accounting/partnership-accounts/admission-of-a-partner/" class="card card-e1" style="flex: 1; padding: 14px 16px; text-decoration: none; color: var(--text); text-align: right;">
              <span style="display: block; font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-3); margin-bottom: 2px;">Next →</span>
              <span style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600;">Admission of a partner</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <aside style="width: 240px; flex-shrink: 0; position: sticky; top: 24px;" class="notes-sidebar">
        <div class="overline" style="font-size: 12px; margin-bottom: 10px;">On this page</div>
        <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; border-left: 2px solid var(--border);">
          <a href="#s1" style="padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--text); font-weight: 650; text-decoration: none; border-left: 2px solid var(--accent); margin-left: -2px;">1. Nature (AS 26)</a>
          <a href="#s2" style="padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-2); text-decoration: none;">2. Average profit</a>
          <a href="#s3" style="padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-2); text-decoration: none;">3. Super profit</a>
          <a href="#s4" style="padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-2); text-decoration: none;">4. Capitalisation</a>
        </div>
        <div class="card" style="margin-top: 24px; padding: 16px;">
          <div style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 650; margin-bottom: 8px;">Your standing</div>
          <Mastery level={0} topicId="p1-ch4-goodwill" />
          <div style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-3); margin-top: 8px; line-height: 1.5;">
            Practising moves this up. No penalty for reading slowly.
          </div>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </main>

  <style>
    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .notes-sidebar { display: none; }
    }
  </style>

  <script>
    import { getMastery } from '../../../../scripts/store.js';
    const labels = ['Not started', 'Familiar', 'Proficient', 'Mastered ✓'];
    const el = document.querySelector('[data-mastery="p1-ch4-goodwill"]');
    if (el) {
      const level = getMastery('p1-ch4-goodwill');
      el.querySelectorAll('.seg').forEach((seg, i) => seg.classList.toggle('on', i < level));
      const label = el.querySelector('[data-mastery-label]');
      if (label) label.textContent = labels[level];
    }
  </script>
</Base>
